quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  2,77,Do they not then know that Allah knows what they conceal and what they make known abroad
  2,78,"And some of them there are, illiterate folk, that know not the Book, but their own fancies, conjectures and idle tales"
  2,79,"But woe to those who write out the Book with their own hands and say \"This is from Allah\"; to buy therewith a little price! And woe to them for what their hands have written, and woe to them for what they gain"
  2,80,"And then they say, \"Hell fire shall not touch us save for a few number of days.\" Say, \"Have you taken a covenant with Allah?\" but Allah breaks not His covenant. Or do you say of Allah that which you do not know"
  2,81,"Nay, whoever gains an evil gain, and is encompassed by his sins, those are the fellows of the Fire, and they shall dwell therein for ever"
  2,82,"But such as act aright, those are the fellows of Paradise, and they shall dwell therein for ever"
  2,83,"And remember when We took from the children of Israel a covenant, saying, \"Serve you none but Allah, and to your two parents show kindness, and to your kindred and the orphans and the needy, and speak to men kindly, and be steadfast in prayer, and gi"